{"questionId":"3515313","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The player has a chance to win money based on how many times they hit the target.</p>\n<p>The gain for the player, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo></math>, is shown in the following table, where a negative gain means that the player loses money.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:113px;border-color:#000000;width:564px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:159px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">x</mi></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:159px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Player’s gain (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">$</mo></math>)<br></strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:60px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3515313","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.12a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
